President Obama hosted the first-ever White House Student Film Festival, showcasing the power of technology in education and announcing $400 million in new private sector commitments towards the ConnectED goal. The commitments include Adobe making $300 million worth of free software available to teachers and students, and Prezi providing $100 million in Edu Pro licenses for high schools and educators across America. The festival featured 16 selected student films, screened in four groups, and a sneak peek of the television series COSMOS: A SPACETIME ODYSSEY. The films covered various topics, such as technology in schools, future innovations, and the use of technology to overcome challenges.